<HEAD justified="center" >
What you should know about TR I FYBA
</HEAD>

<DIV type=1>

<HEAD justified="center" >
Fibrous extract of wheat grain {fiesta Triticum Tricum)
</HEAD>


<BLOCK>
Please read this carefully before you start to take your medicine. If you have any questions or are not sure about anything ask your doctor or pharmacist.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
The name of your medicine is Trifyba. It contains fibrous extract of wheat grain 
<EMPH slant = "italic">
{fiesta Triticum Tricum}. 
</EMPH>
It is used in disorders of the bowel where a high fibre intake is required.
</BLOCK>

<DIV type=2>

<HEAD uline="plain" >
Things to remember about Trifyba
</HEAD>


<BLOCK>
1. Before taking your medicine read the back of this leaflet.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
Take your medicine as directed by your doctor.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
3. The best way to take Trifyba is to mix it with food. It has no taste and will not spoil the flavour of your meal. See "Taking your medicine" on the back of this leaflet.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
